{{Infobox Artwork | image_file=Accademia - Miracle of the Slave by Tintoretto.jpg | title=Miracle of the Slave | artist=[[Tintoretto]] | year=1548 | medium=[[Oil painting|Oil on canvas]] | height_metric=416 | width_metric=544 | metric_unit=cm | imperial_unit=in | city=[[Venice]] | museum=[[Gallerie dell'Accademia]] }}
'''''The Miracle of the Slave''''' (also known as '''''The Miracle of St. Mark''''', 1548) is a painting by the Italian Renaissance artist [[Jacopo Tintoretto]]. Currently housed in the [[Gallerie dell'Accademia]] in [[Venice]], northern Italy, it was originally commissioned for the [[Scuola Grande di San Marco]], a confraternity in the city.
It portrays an episode of the life of [[Saint Mark]], patron saint of Venice, taken from [[Jacopo da Varazze]]'s ''[[Golden Legend]]''. The scene shows, in the upper part, the saint intervening to make invulnerable a slave about to be martyred for his veneration of another saint's relics. All the figures are inscribed into an architectonic scenario.
Different influences on Tintoretto's art can be seen in the picture: while the anatomies are [[Michelangelo]]-like, the vivid and intense colors are typical of the [[Venetian School (art)|Venetian School]].
{{external media | width = 210px | align = right | headerimage=[[File:Jacopo tintoretto, san marco libera uno schiavo, 1547-48, da capitolo della scuola grande di s.marco 11.JPG|210px]] | video1 = [http://smarthistory.khanacademy.org/tintoretto-the-miracle-of-the-slave.html Tintoretto, ''The Miracle of the Slave''], 7:02, [[Smarthistory]]<ref name="smarth">{{cite web | title =Tintoretto, The Miracle of the Slave | work = | publisher =[[Smarthistory]] at [[Khan Academy]] | date = | url =http://smarthistory.khanacademy.org/tintoretto-the-miracle-of-the-slave.html | accessdate =October 10, 2014 }}</ref> }}
